commitResults.messageTitle: Implement feature to display first person on the list whenever list changes
commitResults.messageBody:
So initially when transiting from 'find list' to 'normal list' there was a problem whenever you try to display the same index. For example, if i chose to display index number 5 in the find list, and then hop back over to the normal list and try to display 5 (which may or may not have a different contact at that index now), i would be unnecessarily met with 'index is alr displayed' msg. Therefore i fixed this by resetting the displayed contact to the first one in the list when the list changes.

**Note** Does not affect the functionalities saketh implemented prior which aims to keep the displayed contact constant in the event when contacts are deleted and added
This version returns a contact as long as any one of the fields matches the user inputs
This reverts commit 2fd96fe6b3c56e221ad3c659a8c5343ece909a1b.
Stricter than the find command where the person has to contain all the keywords specified by the user in order to be displayed
